<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-03-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-03-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="1538" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1538">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 723.2515/116.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires at
                                Santiago</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-03-26">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 26, 1910</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Government of the United States, through its Legation at Lima, has
                            been requested to undertake the protection of Peruvian <pb facs="1288" n="1184" xml:id="pg_1184"/> citizens in Chile. The Government of the
                            United States is willing that its Legation exercise its impartial good
                            offices in their behalf. You will, if the Chilean Government consents,
                            act accordingly during the suspension of diplomatic relations. Repeat to
                            Lima for information.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>